>
  <article class="prose">
    <header class="page-header">
      <p class="page-eyebrow">HELP CENTER · LEVEL</p>
      <h1>⛵ Level Growth System Guide</h1>
      <p class="page-lede">
        Open your Voyage Map: 8 islands rise one after another on the horizon. This is LevelUp Land's
        main shipping lane — where day after day of "Today's Voyage" carries you all the way from the
        rookie shallows to the treasure atoll.
      </p>
    </header>

    <h2>What Is the Voyage Map</h2>
    <p>
      Go to <code>/level</code> and you'll find a sea chart unfolding vertically, dotted with 8 islands
      that correspond to your levels, Lv.1 through Lv.8. Each island has one of four states:
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li><strong>Current island</strong> — where you're sailing right now; click it to open the "Today's Voyage" check-in panel;</li>
      <li><strong>Conquered</strong> — an island you've already claimed by completing 30 voyages;</li>
      <li><strong>Locked</strong> — an island still hidden beyond the mist ahead;</li>
      <li><strong>The Misted Horizon</strong> — the unknown waters beyond Lv.8, where new territory will be revealed in the future.</li>
    </ul>
    <p>
      From Driftwood Cove to Treasure Atoll, every island stands witness to a leg of your journey.
    </p>

    <h2>How to Level Up: 30 Voyages to the Next Island</h2>
    <div class="table-wrap"><table>
      <thead><tr><th>Rule</th><th>Details</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>Level-up requirement</td><td>Complete 30 daily check-ins on your current island</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Check-in frequency</td><td>One "Today's Voyage" quest per day</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Total levels</td><td>Lv.1 – Lv.8 open now, with more to come</td></tr>
        <tr><td>Progress display</td><td>Island progress bar (e.g. 17/30) + check-in calendar</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table></div>
    <p>
      Each day's "Today's Voyage" is a lightweight quest — it might be opening the day's chest, watching
      a short video, or completing a social interaction. Finish it and your progress ticks up by 1,
      with the day's Growth Points reward landing instantly.
    </p>

    <h2>Reward Rarities: Persistence Appreciates</h2>
    <p>Daily check-in rewards come in four rarities, and as your streak builds, higher-rarity rewards surface periodically:</p>
    <div class="table-wrap"><table>
      <thead><tr><th>Rarity</th><th>Growth Points</th><th>Typical bonus</th></tr></thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr><td>⚪ Common</td><td>+30 💎</td><td>Standard rations for the daily voyage</td></tr>
        <tr><td>🔵 Rare</td><td>+40 💎</td><td>Bonuses such as +1 Arena draw chance</td></tr>
        <tr><td>🟣 Epic</td><td>+60 💎</td><td>Bonuses such as +2 draw chances</td></tr>
        <tr><td>🟡 Legendary</td><td>+100 💎</td><td>Rare spoils: badges, stacked bonuses, and more</td></tr>
      </tbody>
    </table></div>
    <p>
      Every reward is recorded in your Reward Voyage Log — date, rarity, points, and bonuses at a glance;
      the check-in calendar marks every day you've sailed.
    </p>

    <h2>What Growth Points (💎) Are For</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Growth Points are the universal currency of the entire platform: <strong>rewards from Level check-ins and Quest tasks flow into one and the same balance</strong>;</li>
      <li>Points and levels together form your "voyager profile" — the higher your level and the more points you hold, the richer the partner rewards and platform benefits within your reach;</li>
      <li>More ways to spend points (redemptions, a shop, gameplay tickets, and more) will open as the map expands.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>The Growth Incentive Pool: The Arena's Current Flows Back</h2>
    <blockquote>
      <p>From every round of Arena competition, the platform retains a portion of the funds and channels it into the Growth Incentive Pool — dedicated to rewarding users who keep growing in Level.</p>
    </blockquote>
    <p>
      Which means: every day you persist on the Voyage Map does more than stack points —
      the heat of the entire platform's competition is storing up rewards for those who stay the course.
      As your level rises and your voyage streak milestones fall, rewards from the incentive pool
      (point boosts, Arena Battle Soul tickets, badges, and more) will keep tilting your way.
      Curious where the funds come from? Read the Arena economic model chapter of the
      <a href="/en/whitepaper/">whitepaper</a>.
    </p>

    <h2>How Level Connects with Quest</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>Completing partner bounties on the Quest page also earns Growth Points, accelerating your overall growth;</li>
      <li>Jump from a quest page to Level, complete your check-in, and return to the original quest with one click — the two sea lanes connect seamlessly;</li>
      <li>Some quests appear as "Today's Voyage" in your check-in panel — complete once, and it counts twice.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>FAQ</h2>
    <h3>Q: What happens if I miss a day?</h3>
    <p>Your island progress never rolls back — everything you've banked toward the 30 stays put. But your check-in streak breaks, slowing your path to higher-rarity rewards. Once a day — don't let the ship drop anchor.</p>
    <h3>Q: I completed the check-in quest but it isn't showing — what should I do?</h3>
    <p>Some quests require verification (automatic or manual), so their status briefly shows as "Verifying"; once verified, your progress and points land automatically.</p>
    <h3>Q: What happens after I conquer all 8 islands?</h3>
    <p>Beyond the misted horizon, new territory is already being charted. Your level, points, and voyage log carry over in full — and when the new waters open, veteran captains set sail first.</p>
    <h3>Q: Do Growth Points expire?</h3>
    <p>No. Your point balance never expires, and every change is backed by a complete, auditable ledger.</p>
